pullRequest.body:
Make `IsSeparable` more aligned with `IsIntegral`. Rename previous `IsSeparable` into `Algebra.IsSeparable` (like `Algebra.IsIntegral`), add notation `IsSeparable` for separablity of elements (like `IsIntegral`).

Shorten statements using the new defined `IsSeparable`. Rename some shortened theorems.

@riccardobrasca
I personally think this deserves to be a def. Among other things, it unlocks dot notation.
Good point, let's make it a `def`.

Good! I am working on this. I am also trying to decompose many theorems in `Algebra.IsSeparable` into a theorem of `IsSeparable` and a theorem using the previous one directly. This takes more time that I thought.
What you can do is to open another PR. Here you are just renaming stuff, right? I think it is better to not do anything else in this PR.
